&lt;p&gt;Scopely is looking for an &lt;strong&gt;Accounting Associate&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Finance team in Barcelona on a hybrid basis working 3 days a week from the hub.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Scopely, we care deeply about what we do and want to inspire play, every day - whether in our work environments alongside our talented colleagues, or through our deep connections with our communities of players. We are a global team of game lovers who are developing, publishing and innovating the mobile games industry, connecting millions of people around the world daily.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Show us the money! As the Finance team, we’re number crunchers with top-notch analytical and reporting skills. As a shared service, we get to work with all of Scopely&#39;s talented studios.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an Accounting Associate to join our fast-growing Accounting organization. You will assist in the day-to-day operations of the Accounting team as well as own and manage Accounting initiatives and projects in perpetuity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Accounting Manager to partner with Business Development team to keep track of newly signed development agreements and IP contracts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Revenue team on reconciling the cash receipt on revenues collected and partner to investigate the variances&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate effectively with various teams, subsidiaries, and external auditors to address queries and provide necessary information during audit – internal and IP holder audit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist revenue share/reimbursement calculation for IP holders and Developers on a monthly/quarterly basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad-hoc project as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years experience in accounting, or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s or associate&#39;s degree in accounting, or in a related specialization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, constantly changing environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in working in an international company over multiple locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated history of process improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience working with Oracle will be an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communications skills in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced user of Microsoft Excel and other MS packages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please submit your CV in English.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Scopely, we create games for everyone - and want to ensure that the people behind our games reflect that!&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;We are committed to creating a diverse, supportive work environment where everyone is treated with respect. We are committed to providing equal employment opportunities and welcome individuals from all backgrounds to join us &amp;amp; embrace the adventure!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment at Scopely is based solely on a person&#39;s merit and qualifications. Scopely does not discriminate against any employee or applicant because of race, creed, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition (including breastfeeding), or any other basis protected by law. We also consider qualified applicants with arrest or conviction records, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will have access to sensitive and/or confidential employee or customer personally identifiable information (PII) and/or Company financial information, and therefore will be subject to background checks upon receiving a conditional offer of employment.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&a

&lt;p&gt;Scopely is seeking a highly motivated&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Analytics Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Strategy &amp;amp; Business Operations team in Barcelona on a 2 day a week hybrid basis!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Scopely, we care deeply about what we do and want to inspire play every day - whether in our work environments alongside our talented colleagues or through our deep connections with our communities of players. We are a global team of game lovers who are developing, publishing, and innovating the mobile games industry, connecting millions of people worldwide daily.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Strategy and Business Operations team works closely with the Senior Leadership of Scopely to answer critical business-related questions. By acting as a strategic partner, the team translates complex data into actionable insights that drive the company&#39;s decision-making process and long-term growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and collaborate with engineers, product teams, and analysts to develop self-serve insight products that are responsive, precise, and scalable at petabyte levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the entire data product lifecycle, including designing new tracking plans, developing data models, ELT pipelines, and self-serve insight products like Looker explores and dashboards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a guardian of data quality, ensuring consistent metric reporting across a wide range of data products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize cutting-edge technology stack including BigQuery, dbt and Looker&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical leadership and partner with our stakeholders and their teams to enhance their daily operations and product success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring expertise in a specific part of the data stack and lifecycle while contributing broadly across all aspects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor team members and drive the adoption of best practices within the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong passion for solving complex analytical puzzles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to translate business needs into advanced analytics solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise with the modern data stack (BigQuery, Snowflake, dbt, Looker, Airflow, GitHub, Terraform, command line-based workflows)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional SQL skills coupled with at least 3-4 years of relevant experience in data analytics or engineering roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a solid proficiency in Python, with the ability to write clean, maintainable scripts to automate data workflows, perform exploratory data analysis and integrate various data sources within our modern tech stack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of data modeling principles (e.g., Kimball methodology, star schemas)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A high valuation of business context and the drive to achieve technical excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An inclination towards collaboration and pride in contributing to high-functioning teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoyment in working within fast-paced, growth-oriented environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A sense of fun at work, with extracurricular interests like Ping Pong or Mario Kart seen as a bonus!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
