&lt;li&gt;Own and manage the regional marketing budget, including resource allocation, forecasting, ROI analysis, and optimization against business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish performance goals and KPIs across marketing initiatives, including awareness, acquisition, DAU, WAU, retention, engagement, ARPU, and revenue contribution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data, experimentation, and market insights to evaluate campaign effectiveness and continuously optimize strategies and investments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong relationships with external agencies, platform partners, media partners, and IP stakeholders to maximize marketing impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead organizational planning, recruiting, coaching, and talent development for the marketing team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a collaborative, inclusive, and high-accountability culture that enables teams to execute effectively in a fast-paced global environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate organizational and operational risks proactively and implement scalable processes to support long-term growth.&lt;/li

&lt;p&gt;Scopely is looking for a Director of Product to join an unannounced title working with External Development in our Shanghai office on a hybrid basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Scopely, we care deeply about what we do and want to inspire play, every day - whether in our work environments alongside our talented colleagues, or through our deep connections with our communities of players. We are a global team of game lovers who are developing, publishing and innovating the mobile games industry, connecting millions of people around the world daily.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are in the early stages of development on an ambitious, unannounced AAA mobile game, and we’re assembling a team of passionate game makers to craft unforgettable environments and immersive adventures that players will love.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for developing product strategy for a portion of Scopely’s new game development portfolio to help us have the best chance of a breakout success. You will need to work with our User Insights team, and do qualitative and quantitative analysis on the market/competitive set to form a strong Point of View on where the products of opportunities and threats are. You will then work with our internal game teams to guide them toward the best commercial outcomes and help them answer commercial viability questions during the Greenlight process. You will also have the opportunity to partner with our corporate development team to find the right talent/product mix to add to our slate based on the product strategies you develop. In some cases, you will help the team to form the free-to-play live and monetization strategies during the meta game design phase of the project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with stakeholders and partners worldwide to comprehend market demand, user needs, and competition in order to create a product that fulfills customer expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze Western and Eastern user behavior to derive insights and concepts, and then translate them into product features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and articulate product strategies aligned with business goals and market potential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Determine clear product roadmaps and priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the variances in Western and Chinese product development and navigate the challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set Beta / Soft Launch / Launch KPI’s for the game during development and testing phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business intelligence analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitor’s products tear-down/de-construction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead product and data analytics to comprehend competitor set KPIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Market insight analysis on game genres, user behaviors, and UA trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the global trend of the Chinese gaming industry in terms of both development and publishing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare professional decks for executive-level reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the research team, assist the studio in understanding the gameplay behavior of western users, and translate the product requirements into implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A combination of strong quantitative skills, research capabilities, and F2P/Live operations understanding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert in comp analysis and the ability to quantify what excellence looks like in design/live operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert in modeling P&amp;amp;L from individual product KPI’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be passionate about game development&lt;/li&gt;
